         <abstract>
            <p>We study mesh refinement techniques for first-order hyperbolic equations. A refinement method for use with the leap-frog scheme is defined and its stability established. The remainder of the paper is devoted to a discussion of the effects of nonuniform grids and the circumstances under which they may be used.</p>
          </abstract>
